  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In fact, Constantinople used to be called by the Slav Tsarigrad, the City of the Caesars, Tsarigrad which a lot of people don't know about.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the documents, suddenly you see Tsarigrad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which city are they talking about?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They're talking about Constantinople.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So many of these things, I, I do bring up that way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I know some people dismiss Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Eastern Europe is not important.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Western Europe is important.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This is what one of my colleagues said, you know?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said, well.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, the dictator of Romania, Marshal Antonescu, he protected the Romanian Jews, because the Germans wanted to send them to concentration camps to be killed.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Marshal Antonescu says, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They are our Romanian Jews, and you can't touch them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the only thing that happened to the Jews that they were in work groups working.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they were decently treated, and they were allowed later on to immigrate to Israel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Many, many of my friends are in Israel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Another thing that happened in Eastern Europe was that General Francisco Franco, the leader of Spain-- there are many Jews in Eastern Europe that still speak Spanish, you know?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "During Isabella, they fled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they use the Spanish of Cervantes, you know, Spanish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I was in Spanish [? litigation ?] working in the library there in order to learn Spanish, because I didn't have money to pay for lessons in Spanish, so I worked in the library there.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a Jewish rabbi who came with a group of these Sephardi Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in the old Spanish language of Cervantes, he thanked the ambassador, Spanish ambassador, Condado de Casa Rojas, for saving the Jews by giving them Spanish passports.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
